messages.message:
I pulled from master and got the error. There were a couple of other ppl who also got the same error. 

@Dominic Fannjiang Can you first check in your dependencies folder (mine was in pyenv) if the foundation folder/files exists? If it does, you need to uninstall from pip because it shouldn't be using that one from dependencies. Our update python script doesn't uninstall missing packages. I think this is why your local is working 

If you are indeed using the version bundled in our monorepo, check your build folder's structure for foundation
